The problem here is that both of you have
swallowed whole the Stratfordian scenario
-- with the plays being first produced from
around the mid-1590s onwards, by one
professional company of actors.

Where do you get this story from? Why
do you have such faith in it? On which
actual historical records is it based?

It's based on next to nothing -- it's virtually
all a product of Stratfordian imaginations
-- based largely on the printed quartos as
they came out, from 1594 (anonymously)
and from 1598 (with the name of 'W.Shake-
speare&quot; on about half of them).

